        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 4:22PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gagetown, or near Cass City, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cass City and Gagetown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
